title: Grateful Dead Live at The Scope on 1982-04-03
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Alabama Getaway-> Greatest Story Ever Told, They Love Each Other, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Peggy-O-> CC Rider, Bird Song, It's All Over Now, Althea-> Let It Grow

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Good Time Blues-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Stella Blue-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
It's about time! What a great show. I've bee looking forward to this one for Years!

Thanks (do I even have to rate it? You know that it will be very listenable) Charlie!

Eyes of the World Never heard one like this before. They keep that groove the entire time without fail. Extremely unique rendition.

The whole band firing on all cylinders. A perfect example of that 82' magic. Weir fans will be delighted... listen closely during Me and My Uncle. 

Is this the Phil/Jerry switch show? 

Another crisp CM transfer. Thanks for brining this uncirculated show into the fold.

switch ? They switched the night before in Durham N C .
 People must remember the entire building shaking during Scarlet / Fire on this night. I've felt buildings shaking and grooving along with us from our constant motion dancing but the Scope was unique in that it seemed to bounce along to the rhythm of the song.   Incase anyone wants to read into my comment I do not mean anything more then what it says. this building was rocking .
quality of this version is off the charts.

scarlet/fire>estimated/eyes WOW 2nd set is on fire and one of my favorite Scarlet/Fires. Eyes  is short but so much packed into that short time. Maybe my fave also.Too bad they ended the show kinda lame. I was lucky to have seen that and Duke the night before and Baltimore on that tour. 

5 * for 2nd set.

Really really good show! Grate show! Duke U night be fore so so.
Windy drive up too Norfolk. Scored tickets in the Lot (this were the days).

Really really good show. Love a CC Rider.
Strong 1st set and off the charts 2nd.. 
I remember being on the floor about 1/2 way back and the transition from Scarlet > Fire. The word for it is tantalizing! I was like 'PLAY IT!'.
Good Times came from nowhere and kicked ass.
The whole band was in the groove.
